Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells were fabricated with a 5 mu m thick film of Ce(0.9)Gd(0.1)O(1.95) electrolyte, supported on a NiO-YSZ cermet anode with a La(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3) cathode, for operation at temperatures below 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: The performance for power generation was studied with externally reformed methanol fuel or with methanol/water vapour fed directly to the anode.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: The open-circuit voltages of 0.7-0.8 V were lower than the theoretical potential as a result of electronic permeation across the electrolyte film.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: Maximum power outputs of 126, 65 and 32 mW/cm(2) were obtained at 650, 600 and 550 degrees C respectively, using the externally reformed fuel.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: With direct methanol fuel the maximum power output was lower at each temperature by 16, 38 and 53%, respectively.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: The latter result at 550 degrees C was due to the poor internal reforming of methanol to hydrogen at the anode.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels

Sentencas: The addition of Pd to the anode promoted the internal reforming at 550 degrees C: the maximum power output was similar to the previous result with externally reformed fuel and 45% lower with direct methanol fuel.
Titulo: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated with methanol fuels
